When communism fell apart in 1989 Bulgaria and the Iron Curtain was dissolved, one of the first Western series they played on television was David Lynch's "Twin Peaks". My Soviet era truck driver and factory worker grandfather and semi-illiterate village grandma watched it. Wild.

Imagine Twin Peaks being one of your first exposures to raw unmediated Western culture. My other grandparents watched it too. Probably how people in North Korea right now feel at those k-pop concerts they staged there a few years ago. Reunification always arrives as a catastrophe

The real life will only start when the number of the living is greater than the number of the dead, like back in the times of Cain and Seth. Chesterton said tradition is a democracy where the dead vote, but maybe the world will feel less of a graveyard when we outvote them again.

Many of the dead vote for Dagon, Baal, and Obama, it's high time we outnumber them and vote their candidates out of the polls. This is what Project Megatherians was about in Gene Wolfe's BoTNS, settling the stars out to regain an autonomy of the living, seek self-determination.
